        <div xml:id="Kali30-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">itu paruvavaraviṉkaṇ āṟṟāta talaimakaḷ iṟantatu cintittu nammāṭṭu aṉpilarāyiṉum 
            ikkālattu ivvūriṉkaṭ paṇṭu tām viḷaiyāṭiya-vāṟu niṉaintu varuvar ikkālavaravu colluvār uḷarāyiṉeṉak 
            kēṭṭa pāṇaṉ pācaṟaikkaṭ ceṉṟu talaivaṉaik kaṇṭu kūṟiyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en"/>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="Kali30">
            <lg type="edition">
                <l>aruntava māṟṟiyār nukarccipō laṇikoḷa</l>
                <l>virintāṉāc ciṉaitoṟūum vēṇṭuntā tamarntāṭip</l>
                <l>purintārkkum vaṇṭoṭu pulamputīrn tevvāyu</l>
                <l>miruntumpi yiṟaikoḷa vetiriya vēṉilāṉ;</l>
                <l rend="space">tuyiliṉṟi yānīntat toḻuvaiyam puṉalāṭi</l>
                <l>mayiliyalār maruvuṇṭu maṟantamaiku vāṉmaṉṉō</l>
                <l>veyiloḷi yaṟiyāta virimalart taṇkāviṟ</l>
                <l>kuyilālum poḻuteṉak kūṟuna ruḷarāyiṉ;</l>
                <l rend="space">pāṉāḷyām paṭarkūrap paṇaiyeḻi laṇaimeṉṟōṇ</l>
                <l>māṉōkki ṉavaroṭu maṟantamaiku vāṉmaṉṉō</l>
                <l>vāṉāccīrk kūṭalu ḷarumpaviḻ naṟumullait</l>
                <l>tēṉārkkum poḻuteṉat teḷikkuna ruḷarāyiṉ</l>
                <l>uṟaliyā moḷivāṭa vuyarntavaṉ viḻaviṉuḷ</l>
                <l>viṟaliḻai yavaroṭu viḷaiyāṭu vāṉmaṉṉō</l>
                <l>peṟalarum poḻutoṭu piṟaṅkiṇart turutticūḻn</l>
                <l>taṟalvārum vaiyaiyeṉ ṟaṟaiyuna ruḷarāyiṉ;</l>
                <l rend="space">eṉavāṅku,</l>
                <l>taṇiyānō yuḻantāṉāt takaiyava ṭakaipeṟa</l>
                <l>vaṇikiḷar neṭuntiṇṭē rayarmati paṇipuniṉ</l>
                <l>kāmar kaḻalaṭi cērā</l>
                <l>nāmañcā ṟevvari ṉaṭuṅkiṉaḷ peritē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="4">            In summer which is imminent so that dark bees take [their] seats </l>
<l corresp="3">everywhere, loneliness ending, together with bees that humm desirously, </l>
<l corresp="2">dancing, settling on the pollen they want on every branch that does not end opening [blossoms] </l>
<l corresp="1">decoratively like the enjoyment of those capable of difficult penance, </l>
<l rend="space">Bathing in the pretty flood in the pool where we swam without sleep,</l>
<l>will be be content forgetting, after having consumed the embraces of those with peacock nature?</l>
<l>– in cool groves with expanding blossoms that do not know the brightness of the sunlight,</l>
<l>if there are those who will tell [him]: “it is the time when the koels call.”  </l>
<l rend="space">While we abound in affliction at midnight, will he be content forgetting</l>
<l>[out] graceful bamboo shoulders soft to touch with those who have the glances of deer?</l>
<l>– if there are those to make it clear that it is the time when bees hum</l>
<l>on the fragrant jasmine opening [its] buds in Kūṭal of unending excellence.</l>
<l rend="space">While we, suffering, fade in brightness, will he play </l>
<l>with those who have superior jewels in the festival of the high one?</l>
<l>– if there are those who announce that the Vaiyai overflows the black sand,</l>
<l>surrounding the islets with glistening clusters at a time difficult to get.</l>
<l rend="space">That is to say,</l>
<l rend="space">So that she who is suited [to you] who unendingly suffers pain that won’t calm down obtains [her] beauty [again],</l>
<l>prepare the tall firm chariot shining with ornaments.</l>
<l>like the enemies full of fear who don’t humbly join </l>
<l>your desirable ankleted feet she has come to shiver greatly. </l>
            </lg>
        </div>
